originalText.text: Ive been going to Martion and Reagan for years with the best possible results every time with great care and humor from both Doctors even when I arrive with no appointment.  Can not recommend this practice highly enough!

originalText.text:
Today is 12/7/2020. I've been trying to get in touch with the office since 10/19 to make an appointment because this is the only office in walking distance of my apartment that's in network with my insurance.

10/19 I called and got the voicemail, left a message and also dropped an email to the address on their website, no reply. 2 weeks later I tried again another voicemail, no response.  After having two back surgeries last year I'm doing my best to be proactive about my health so I don't regress to the level of pain I was in for most of last year so it's devastating that I can't even get a response from anyone at the practice.

As a last measure, I came to the address listed at 2:30 on a Monday, the office hours on the website and voicemail are 11-7 M-Th.  The office is located on the 1st floor of 33 Greenwich street. I arrived and the door is locked, there is no reception desk other than for the building residents and the doorman told me they re-open at 3:00. I waited 40 minutes until 3:10 and no one showed up.

Needless to say this is borderline medical negligence.

originalText.text:
I had debilitating sciatic pain in my back... I couldn't even walk- I came here and after the first visit felt immediate improvement... had to go a few more times and am so happy I did.
I'd highly recommend to anyone suffering from back area nerve pain.
